Defendant in custody.  
Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of eight (8) years on each count, concurrent, imposed and stayed.   Three (3) years initial confinement, followed by five (5) years extended supervision.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for five (5) years on each count concurrent.   Conditions of probation are:
1) On Count 2, spend one (1) year in the Manitowoc County Jail, under the Huber Law, to commence immediately;
2) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination;
3) Obtain HSED/GED;
4) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
5) Pay costs of action; 
6) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
7) Pay DNA surcharge;
8) Speak to high schools on one occasion with their permission regarding the dangers of drugs;
9) Visit the grave site of Nathan Farr on the date of his death.
Defendant is eligibile for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.   
Defendant is entitled to 192 days sentence credit.   
